<h2>Installing the Coq proof assistant</h2>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Download and install the last version of Coq (from sources or with binaries): <a href="http://coq.inria.fr/download">http://coq.inria.fr/download</a></li>
<li>Install an IDE for interacting with Coq
  <ul>
    <li>a standalone IDE distributed with Coq (easier for beginners
    but difficult to install on some platforms): <a href="http://www.lix.polytechnique.fr/coq/coqide-screenshots?id=1">CoqIDE</a></li>
    <li>a Emacs mode: <a href="http://proofgeneral.inf.ed.ac.uk/download">Proof General</a></li>
  </ul>
</li>
</ul>
</p>

